<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px"><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post23981"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 09-09-2003, 11:43 PM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=23981&amp;postcount=9" target="new"><strong>9</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_23981">MellenFC</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div><br /> those first bought ones are augmentations for your charm.. I think the way it works out is final stats for your charm is  Charm stats + augmentation stats.<br />
<br />
Charm stats are varied depending on the conditions of the charm (ie: it raining in the current zone, have an illusion up etc.)  Augmenation stats would be the same, the ones you buy their condition is that you be in a ldon zone so pretty sure those particular charm augmentations do only work in ldon zones.  <br />
<br />
They seem to be junk ones though anyways.  I think you're meant to use the adventurer's stone charm augmenation with the pop charm to get a good effect.  The condition on that one is that it gets stronger as you learn more from the wayfarers.  The learning them seems to be like a ldon flag.  Got a msg along those lines for every 2 completed adventures when you hail the appropriate person back in the wayfarer's camp.  Think 2 completed adventures in all 5 dungeons = a set of stat increases on that augmentation. <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=23981"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_23981_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">MellenFC</td></tr></table></div></div>
