<table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post23982"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 09-10-2003, 11:21 PM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=23982&amp;postcount=10" target="new"><strong>10</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_23982">SuburbanLife</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div><br /> From what I have gathered about Augments are....<br />
<br />
<strong>Type 1</strong> - these are going to be your stat upgrades to items such as +hp, +mana, gains in saves, wis/int/sta etc.<br />
<br />
<strong>Type 2</strong> - these will be upgrades such as Flowing Thought, Regeneration, Atk upgrades<br />
<br />
<strong>Type 3</strong> - this is just a guess, but I would imagine something such as focus effects like mana pres, improved healing, etc<br />
<br />
<strong>Type 4</strong> - found on weapons, these will add procs<br />
<br />
If I am a lil wrong feel free to upgrade, this is just second hand info from my brother who beta tested it.<br />
<br />
 <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=23982"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_23982_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">SuburbanLife</td></tr></table></div>
